transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs),1 are fatal neurodegenerative disorders that include Kuru, Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD), and Gerstman-Straussler-Scheinker (GSS) disease in man. Central to the pathogenesis of TSEs is the conversion of the host-encoded cellular prion protein (PrPC) into -sheet-rich disease-related isoforms (PrPSc)
